{
  "stem": "14168.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Becoming the leader of Betar.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, I had not.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[BACKROUND NOISE] We had-- I joined the Zionist movement in about 1933.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I belonged, at that time, to a fraternity-- students' fraternity.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ivria.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I-V-R-I-A.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And later on, it was named [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ivria means Hebrew-- the Hebrew Association.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And [INAUDIBLE] means the dawn.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In-- no, no.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Ivria-- a Hebrew word in English means Hebrew-- the Hebrew association.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in-- and later on, it was named [INAUDIBLE] in Hebrew, and-- which is dawn, I think, in English.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I had, in fact, debated the Zionist issue with friends of mine very, very vividly before 1933.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I had thought that the solution of what was called the Jewish problem would be in assimilation, in-- and in a greater understanding and a progress of humanity towards a-- against prejudice.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But, of course, that proved to be nothing but an illusion.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And then I remembered those discussions when Hitler came, and I decided I have to change my views.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I have to recognize reality.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And it's-- and-- and-- and-- and be conscious of my Jewish identity.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was very much interested in Zionism, but I-- very frankly, I was not too persuaded that the Zionism which the venerable and venerated Professor Weizmann, at the time, preached-- namely, give in to Great Britain and follow Great Britain and don't make much noise, you know, otherwise, it'll get worse-- that that would get us anywhere.",
      "word_count": 58
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was afraid that, also-- that the thought of creating a Jewish State-- a majority of Jews, which was a core of [INAUDIBLE]-- that that was getting lost and being diluted.",
      "word_count": 32
    }
  ],
